  "text": "In cat primary auditory cortex horizontal connections generally follow a course parallel to the iso-frequency contours [CITATION_1] ) but others project in directions orthogonal to the iso-frequency contours and may even extend as far as anterior and posterior auditory fields [CITATION_2] . Strengthening of the horizontal connections after kindling may explain the larger percentage of double-tuned frequency tuning curves that we observed. If these horizontal connections become stronger than those of the specific thalamic inputs, they could elicit an outward migration of glutamate hyperactivity and subsequent synaptic changes. This process would likely stop when all the neurons in the stimulated cortical area (and its projection region) were combined into one large neural assembly.",
